            "body": "<blockquote>\n  <p>But there is no such method defined in the java.util.Map interface!<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>There <em>is<\/em> a <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/Map.html#remove-java.lang.Object-java.lang.Object-\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>Map#remove(Object, Object)<\/code><\/a> method in the <code>Map<\/code> interface; it was added in Java 8. Hence the error.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 23785923,
            "question_id": 23785807
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-MOFiRVQAjRc/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAB8/yiVh7YTu-ks/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
                "account_id": 2736951,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 2359424,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2359424/devjalvarezrom",
                "reputation": 2964,
                "display_name": "devjalvarezrom"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 2,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1400828271,
            "creation_date": 1400701294,
            "body": "<p>This is due <strong>type erasure<\/strong> process when a java generic type is translated to bytecode.<\/p>\n\n<p>At runtime the <code>default boolean remove(Object key, Object value)<\/code> (this method is new in Java 8) in Map is the same than your method at MultiMap class <code>public boolean remove(K key, V value)<\/code>. <\/p>\n\n<p>The compiler sees this, and hence shows the error :<\/p>\n\n<p><em>Name clash: The method remove(K,V) of type MultiMap has the same erasure as remove(Object, Object) of type AbstractMap but does not \n override it.<\/em><\/p>\n\n<p>See this: <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/generics/genTypes.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/generics/genTypes.html<\/a><\/p>\n",
